Whether it&#039;s a captain on each team banning 5 or one ban per person, there is no reason.

&quot;Entire champion pools get banned out&quot;
Learn more than 10 champions. It&#039;s not that hard.

&quot;They could ban out every meta pick&quot;
Stop being a meta following sheep, and again, LEARN MORE THAN 10 CHAMPIONS.

&quot;One single role could get banned out&quot;
Firstly, that means the other 4 roles are completely untouched, which will almost never happen. And I can still easily list 10 champions I could play in my main role.

And before anyone asks, {{champion:120}} {{champion:9}} {{champion:30}} {{champion:121}} {{champion:64}} {{champion:57}} {{champion:11}} {{champion:2}} {{champion:56}} {{champion:80}} {{champion:421}} {{champion:154}} {{champion:77}} {{champion:5}}. That is more than 10 and not the only champions I can play in the jungle. If you really main a role and are good at it, then you can play more than the same 2 champions.

There are 123 champions. We get 6 bans. You can ban out less than 5% of the champions. Consider that half are nowhere near ban worthy, that puts it at 10% of &#039;ban worthy&#039; champions. And with 10 bans, there would only be 8% of the champion pool banned, with around 16% &#039;ban worthy,&#039; or if you only consider a small portion ban worthy, then upward to 32%, IF you consider only 1/4 of the champions to be worth a ban at all (not saying OP, just annoying enough to merit a ban).

